<br>
Troll guards in Rathe Mountians<br>
<br>
There are 2 guards. At 45 I doubt you can keep up with the spawn but they pull single flawlessly and you can simply go at your own pace. One is a Shadowknight and the other is a Shaman. About a 6 minute spawn on each one. If I got there and the place was empty I'd do the SK first. Earth pet, BOII and flame shielded. Stay way back... not centered between the 2 guards but well off to the side of the guard you are pulling. Send pet... DO NOT CAST! You want pet to take that Harm Touch. Once in a great while the SK will whack you with it instead of pet. Very surviveable at 45, but it's still nasty. After pet is actively beating on SK... Malisement... pause... then Shock of Swords. Check pet health... heal if needed ...shock him once more. If you have a good earthie summoned I think that's all it will take. You might want to keep a small nuke memmed (like Blaze) to finish the fight without wasting a ton. Once in a while you MAY agro the guard. Run through your pet like usual and he should come right off and get back on pet.<br>
<br>
I FLEW through 45 here and stayed (on and off) through 47. It's worth it to be here even if you have to share the spawn and just do one guard. It's safe here. No trains come through. I just backed way up and camped and stayed here for days.<br>
<br>
Deepwater Baracuda in Lake of Ill Omen<br>
<br>
You heard right. Fish. Lake of Ill Omen is kind of well known for the Bloodgill Goblin spawns out in the middle of the lake. NOBODY hunts the fish. There's a structure underwater with like 4 towers or platforms at .. well.... at the 4 corners of the structure. The platform CLOSEST to where the stream comes in from Firiona Vie... like swim straight out the stream... has a static spawn to the right. It's like a 40 second spawn. Only singles. No runners. No trains. But you ARE underwater so have lots of Waterstones. Kill ONLY Deepwater Baracuda if you're solo at 45. Once in a while a Bloodgill Baracuda will spawn. Don't even TRY him at 45. If you have a partner you can probably kill him, but not solo until 49 or higher. These took me through 48, 49 and into 50 where there were just so many greens. People came to camp the Bloodgill Gobs and ignored these EXCELLENT sources of exp.<br>
