<br>
Also, at 44, seafuries. These will take you into 51 (possibly beyond) as well.  Yes, there are people out there who say that it's impossible to solo a seafury at 44.  Prove them wrong!<br>
Oh, and spirocs (Timorous Deep).  At 44, you'll need a group for these, since multiple pulls are somewhat frequent, but at 49 (assuming that you have jboots), you'll be able to take 2 with no problem.  Just put the pet on one, if the other follows you, take off running, circle back, drop a heal on the pet or a nuke on the one the pet is fighting, repeat till it's dead, then watch the pet unleash it's holy rage on the thing that's been chasing it's master around.  There are 4 types.  One which greens out at 49-50, one which starts to green out at 52 (thanks, Desjardins), one which we don't know when it greens out (yet), and one which IS level 50, but he's easy to avoid - just don't climb any rocks.  Also, lev rings are a MUST for pulling (and watch for roamers).  I take no responsibility if you try to do these things pre-49 without at least a partner! <p><table width="100%" border="0">
